    {
      "Text": "Security update for python-Pillow",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for python-Pillow fixes the following issues\n\n- CVE-2026-42308: integer overflow in font processing can lead to denial of service (bsc#1265359).\n- CVE-2026-42309: heap buffer overflow when processing nested list coordinates (bsc#1265153).\n- CVE-2026-42310: infinite loop and resource exhaustion when processing specially crafted PDFs (bsc#1265154).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
